What does the following code print?

double x = 0.1 + 0.2;
double y = 0.3;
System.out.println(x == y);

What does the following code print?

int x = 0;
boolean result = (x != 0) && (10 / x > 2);
System.out.println(result);

What does the following code print?

int a = 5;
boolean test = (a > 10) && (++a > 5);
System.out.println(a);

What does the following code print?

int b = 5;
boolean test = (b < 10) || (++b > 5);
System.out.println(b);

What does the following code print?

int score = 75;
String result = (score >= 60) ? "Pass" : "Fail";
System.out.println(result);

What is the value of max after this code executes?

int a = 10, b = 20;
int max = (a > b) ? a : b;

